<br>
That is basically exactly an example of the new 'challenges' proposed by these rulesets.  Somethings are now going to be very difficult.  <br>
<br>
Others will become eaiser (with the removal of the NO DROP tag, players can now sell, give, trade everything - you might stumple upon your needed piece that used to be NO DROP on a merchant or from another player, which would eliminate your need to camp for it). <br>
<br>
If I may add to your senerio about the Brownie outcast.  What if the high level 'guard' player needed stacks of swirling mists (not sure if it is TLC affected).   The I am sure they would gladly exchange 6 hours of guard duty for a stack or two of swirling mists, which was TLC to him.  <br>
<br>
It may not always be so 'neat' a transaction, but it is just a simple example of lower players coorperating with higher players to a mutually rewarding relationship (rather than the Highlevel players dominating).<br>
