<br>
You and Chip both brought up the fact that some of these quests arent impossible to do. I cannot argue with that. But I think its reasonable to assume a certain level of difficulty (or range of difficulty) for players to encounter when doing quests and I honestly feel the TLC, in its current form, makes some quests unacceptably difficult.<br>
<br>
Now, I know this is subjective. But I think I can offer a fair judgement having completed an epic quest for my character and helped completed over 20 other epics for folks in and outside our guild. Those included the dreaded necro, cleric and mage epic quests to the incredibly easy shaman epic quest. After doing those and going through the motions and long camps I can honeslty say I feel that some of these quests affected by TLC aren't reasonable.<br>
<br>
I can't stress to you enough that its not my wish to have TLC removed. I just want it modified. Thats how I voted  btw, on that poll to keep TLC , remove it, or modify it. You know what I really want? I mean getting all this feedback and different point of views from you guys was great. But what I really want is some word from Verant that they are either &quot;yes&quot; working on an alternate form of TLC like Brad said they would, or &quot;no&quot; they arent.<br>
<br>
That way I could have something to look forward to or just finally shut up about all this TLC nonsense. I'm to old and tired to keep arguing about this. In the mean time, as a chanter I can mem blur mobs. So if anyone needs help with a trivial item I will be more than willing to help.<br>
<br>
Not bitter, really...just tired.<br>
